article.headline: Drake 61, S. Illinois 51
article.story: DES MOINES, Iowa (AP) -- Josh Young scored 24 points to lead Drake past Southern Illinois 61-51 Wednesday night, matching the Bulldogs' best-ever start and snapping a 17-game losing streak against the Salukis. Young was 7-of-10 from the floor, including 2-of-4 from 3-point range. The Bulldogs (11-1, 2-0 Missouri Valley) were leading 47-43 when he sparked an 11-2 run with three free throws and a steal for a layup. Leonard Houston then added a layup and Adam Emmenecker sank four free throws for a 58-45 lead with 2:35 remaining. Klayton Korver scored 13 points and Houston added 12 points and seven rebounds for the Bulldogs, who have won 10 straight. Wesley Clemmons scored 13 points for Southern Illinois (6-7, 1-1), 11 coming in the first half. Bryan Mullins added nine points. Trailing early, Drake went on a 7-0 run capped by a 16-foot fall-away jumper by Young to give the Bulldogs a 14-8 lead. Drake, which has led at halftime in every game, led 27-22 at the break. The last time the Bulldogs were 11-1 was the 1969-70 season, and the last time they beat Southern Illinois was on Feb. 17, 1999 -- a 64-60 triumph.
